  "prompt": "How many degrees of crankshaft rotation does it take to complete one complete engine cycle in a 4 stroke engine?",
  "response": "In a 4-stroke engine, one complete engine cycle consists of four distinct strokes: intake, compression, power (combustion), and exhaust. Completing all these strokes requires two full rotations of the crankshaft. Since one rotation of the crankshaft is 360 degrees, two rotations would be 720 degrees. Therefore, it takes 720 degrees of crankshaft rotation to complete one complete engine cycle in a 4-stroke engine.",
